Publicker Industries Inc saidits will receive an unqualified opinion on 1986 financialstatements from auditor Arthur Andersen and Co and the opinionon its 1985 statements will be changed to unqualified fromqualified.    The company said the 1985 opinion had been qualified due tothe uncertainty of the ultimate amount recoverable from theassets of its British beverage division.  It said it has beenin the process of substantially reducing its inventory ofScotch whisky and intends to complete the reduction by the endof 1987.  It said it expects to recover its 12 mln dlrinvestment in the division by the end of the year. Reuter&#3;